Related: #12 #24
Adds:

 Xdebug to PHP (Backend)
 Byebug to Ruby (Backend)
 Material Design to CSS Frameworks (Frontend)

I'm making this PR to include some Linux and Unix distributions that are ideal for web servers as not all distributions are suitable to be used in a production server and it can be hard to choose one if you're new to Linux.
I've also added Emacs as a text editor since it has some amazingly powerful features and it's the closest contendant to Vim.
Because the tech industry isn't for males only.
The names were cutoff so I updated the spacing so its clear.
In Understand the concepts under Javascript Basics, I wondered whether "Hosting" meant "Hoisting".  So I'm proposing this amendment.

Hi, Kamran.
I took the liberty of doing a translation of your roadmap in Brazilian Portuguese and I am sending a pull request to approve it who knows in a separate branch. I will also open an issue so that other Brazilians can contribute with improvements and corrections.
Thanks! ^^

Infrastructure monitoring tool - prometheus is used very prominently by most of the companies as it helps monitor multiple metrics using a single agent called exporter. I think adding prometheus would be apt as this is one of a kind in this list.
According to issue #625, SASS shouldn't be referenced as SASS, but as Sass.
